comments: Replay review of the foul called on Vucevic (CHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Vucevic (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Ross (ORL) and cleanly blocks the shot.
Wagner (ORL) brings his hand towards White (CHI) on the perimeter, and marginal contact occurs as he releases away.
LaVine (CHI) avoids making contact with Ross' (ORL) arm during his contest on the jump shot attempt.
Wagner (ORL) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from DeRozan (CHI) at the end of the drive.
Although Harris (ORL) initially makes clean ball contact, his hand slides off of the ball and onto DeRozan's (CHI) wrist, which affects his ability to pass the ball.
LaVine (CHI) slides his hand off of Ross' (ORL) chest and marginal contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (ORL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Ball (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Wagner (ORL).
Hampton (ORL) reaches in and makes contact with LaVine's (CHI) arm, which affects his SQBR and disrupts his dribble.
Hampton (ORL) brings his off-arm towards Vucevic's (CHI) vertical arm, and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Wagner (ORL) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
Harris (ORL) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
Harris (ORL) enters the three-point arc before the release of DeRozan's (CHI) free throw attempt.
LaVine (CHI) briefly grasps Wagner's (ORL) shorts during rebounding.
After inbounding the ball, Wagner (ORL) establishes himself inbounds and legally gains possession.

Ball (CHI) jumps forward towards Wagner (ORL) and makes contact with Wagner's lower body, which affects his jump shot attempt. Wagner does not abandon his shot or launch himself into Ball to draw the contact.
Wagner (ORL) commits a take foul on LaVine (CHI).
Jones Jr. (CHI) turns into Ross' (ORL) path and makes leg to leg contact that affects his SQBR.
All Flagrant Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.

During the inbound, Hampton (ORL) engages with DeRozan (CHI) and marginal contact occurs as he briefly grasps and immediately releases his off-arm, which does not affect his ability to get to the inbounds pass.
During the inbound, LaVine (CHI) and Harris (ORL) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Hampton (ORL) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
White (CHI) legally contests Harris' (ORL) jump shot attempt.
